<title>BOTSWANA: FNB raises yr shr, div increased.</title>
<headline>FNB raises yr shr, div increased.</headline>
<dateline>GABORONE 1997-05-21</dateline>
<text>
<p>Half year ended March 31</p>
<p>		    (million pula unless stated)</p>
<p>    Shr (thebe)			49.0    vs    44.0</p>
<p>    Div (thebe)			13.0    vs    11.5</p>
<p>    After tax			12.395    vs    11.252</p>
<p>    Net income		     42.575    vs    37.595</p>
<p>    Net interest income	  29.246    vs    26.482</p>
<p>    Other operating income     15.512    vs    12.154</p>
<p>    Bad/doubtful debt charge    2.183    vs    1.101</p>
<p>    Pre-tax			  16.526    vs    15.003</p>
<p>    Tax				 4.132    vs    3.751</p>
<p>Full name: First National Bank of Botswana Limited</p>
<p>Div payable June 20 1997</p>
<p>On register June 6 1997</p>
<p>NOTE - The bank said advances had grown by 4.6 percent against a market that in total had declined, but with a growth in deposits of 28.2 percent the bank was well positioned to participate in lending opportunities when they arose.</p>
<p>The charge for bad debts had grown significantly against the comparable period last year, but at 0.76 percent of advances, it was well within acceptable norms.</p>
<p>-- Gaborone newsroom +267 347182</p>
